| header file "SingleLogicalResult.h" and involve contorting bool. At least
| that's as far as I can dechiper the errors.

Could be: any() is an Rcpp function, which has to follow the R standard of
having _three_ logical values TRUE, FALSE, and NA.  

That does not map to C++'s 'bool', so you need to wrap the any() inside of an
is_true() to get 'bool' of either TRUE or FALSE.  I think we talk about this
in the sugar vignette.

I saw your post on SO, and the decent vectorised non-Rcpp solution you get
thanks to user flodel.  Let's now see where we get with Rcpp -- it may not be
much faster, but it is a useful learning example for you.

Dirk
 
